@startuml
title Diagrama de Secuencia - Editar Curso
actor "Administrador" as Admin
participant "Frontend (React)" as FE
participant "API (FastAPI)" as API
participant "CursoService" as Service
participant "CursoRepository" as Repo
database "Base de Datos" as DB
Admin -> FE: Clic en "Editar" (en una fila)
activate FE
FE --> Admin: Mostrar Formulario con datos precargados
Admin -> FE: Modifica datos y Guardar
FE -> API: PUT /cursos/{id} (CursoUpdate JSON)
activate API
API -> Service: editar_curso(id, curso_update)
activate Service
Service -> Repo: get_by_id(id)
activate Repo
Repo -> DB: SELECT * FROM cursos WHERE id = ?
activate DB
DB --> Repo: Curso existente
deactivate DB
Repo --> Service: Curso
deactivate Repo
Service -> Service: Actualizar campos
Service -> Repo: update(curso)
activate Repo
Repo -> DB: UPDATE cursos SET ... WHERE id = ?
activate DB
DB --> Repo: OK
deactivate DB
Repo --> Service: Curso actualizado
deactivate Repo
Service --> API: CursoResponse
deactivate Service
API --> FE: 200 OK (Curso JSON)
deactivate API
FE -> FE: Actualizar Lista / Notificar Éxito
FE --> Admin: Mostrar "Curso actualizado correctamente"
deactivate FE
@enduml
